**Sources:** Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers (SIAM) [siam.in](https://www.siam.in); industry flash reports cited in Economic Times and Automotive News

## Appendix C: Key FTA Tariff Provisions for the Automotive Sector

### Tariff Schedule Comparison

| **Vehicle Category** | **Pre-FTA Tariff** | **Post-FTA (Immediate)** | **Long-term Target** | **Annual Quota** |
|---------------------|-------------------|------------------------|---------------------|------------------|
| ICE vehicles >€15,000 | Up to 110% | 40% | 10% (timeline TBD) | 200,000 units |
| ICE vehicles <€15,000 | Up to 110% | 110% (no change) | TBD | Not applicable |
| Battery EVs (BEVs) | 110% | **110% (excluded)** | **Excluded 5 years** | 0 units |
| Plug-in Hybrids (PHEVs) | 110% | TBD | TBD | TBD |

### Existing Indian EV Policy Requirements
- **Domestic Value Addition:** 
  - Year 3 of operations: 25% minimum
  - Year 5 of operations: 50% minimum
- **PLI Scheme Allocation:** ₹25,938 crore ($3.1 billion) for automotive and auto-component manufacturing
- **Battery Manufacturing PLI:** Additional ₹18,100 crore ($2.4 billion) for Advanced Chemistry Cell (ACC) production

**Sources:** FTA negotiation briefings as reported by Economic Times, CNBC, Moneycontrol; Indian Department of Heavy Industry PLI scheme documentation

## Appendix D: FTA Negotiation Timeline & Implementation Status

- **Negotiations Began:** 2007
- **Negotiations Concluded:** January 27, 2026
- **Duration:** 18 years of negotiation
- **Next Steps:** 
  - Legal scrubbing and translation of agreement text (estimated 3-4 months)
  - Formal signing ceremony (expected June-July 2026)
  - Ratification by European Parliament and Council
  - Ratification by Indian Union Cabinet and Parliament
  - Full implementation expected Q1-Q2 2027

**Current Status (as of January 27, 2026):** Agreement announced; text finalization in progress

**Sources:** European Commission press releases; Indian Ministry of External Affairs statements; Moneycontrol reporting

## Appendix E: India's Electric Vehicle Market Context

### Current Market Statistics
- **Current Annual Luxury EV Sales:** Approximately 2,000 units
- **Luxury Segment Electrification Rate:** 10.7%
- **Mass Market Electrification Rate:** 4.5%
- **Total EV Sales (2025):** ~198,000 units (4.5% of total passenger vehicle market)
- **Market Leader:** Tata Motors (~70% market share in EVs)
- **Chinese EV Manufacturers Operating in India:** BYD, MG Motor India (SAIC subsidiary)

### Battery Production Capacity

| **Region/Country** | **Current Capacity (2025)** | **Projected 2030** | **Global Share (2025)** |
|-------------------|---------------------------|-------------------|------------------------|
| China | 1,000+ GWh | ~2,000 GWh | ~75% |
| European Union | ~150 GWh | ~500 GWh | ~11% |
| United States | ~130 GWh | ~450 GWh | ~9% |
| South Korea | ~80 GWh | ~150 GWh | ~6% |
| **India** | **<10 GWh** | **100-120 GWh (target)** | **<1%** |

### Policy Targets (NITI Aayog EV Roadmap)
- **2030 EV Penetration Target:** 30% of all vehicle sales
- **Projected 2030 Market Size:** 7-8 million total vehicles
- **Implied 2030 EV Sales:** 2.1-2.4 million units
- **Required Battery Capacity (2030):** 100-120 GWh for domestic consumption alone

**Sources:** International Energy Agency Global EV Outlook 2025; Bloomberg NEF Battery Supply Chain Database; NITI Aayog reports; SIAM data

## Appendix F: Regulatory Framework References

### EU Regulations Relevant to FTA
- **Battery Regulation:** (EU) 2023/1542 - Battery passport, lifecycle carbon accounting, due diligence requirements
- **Vehicle General Safety Regulation:** (EU) 2019/2144 - Software updates, cybersecurity requirements
- **Carbon Border Adjustment Mechanism (CBAM):** Phase 2 (2026-2034) - Embedded carbon tariffs on imports
- **General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):** (EU) 2016/679 - Data handling for connected vehicles

### Indian Regulations and Standards
- **Automotive Industry Standard (AIS):** Bureau of Indian Standards vehicle certification
- **Information Technology Act (2000):** Data localization and privacy requirements
- **Production-Linked Incentive (PLI) Scheme:** Domestic value addition requirements
- **National Electric Mobility Mission Plan (NEMMP):** 2030 electrification targets

**Sources:** EUR-Lex official legal database; Bureau of Indian Standards; Department of Heavy Industry

